<main class="w-full bg-[#efefef] px-4 pt-28 pb-16">
  <section class="mx-auto grid min-h-[82vh] max-w-7xl grid-cols-[1.15fr_0.85fr] gap-12 border-b border-slate-300 pb-14 max-lg:grid-cols-1">
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-end">
      <p class="font-lexend text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-amber-600">
        Backend / platform / reliable data systems
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-6 max-w-5xl font-lexend text-7xl font-bold leading-[0.95] tracking-normal text-slate-950 max-xl:text-6xl max-md:text-5xl">
        I build backend systems where data stays correct under load, retries, and failure.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-8 max-w-3xl text-2xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700 max-md:text-xl">
        I build backend platforms, event-driven workers, query paths, and observability surfaces for systems where duplicate work, delayed jobs, data drift, and partial failure have to be handled correctly.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3 font-lexend text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-700">
        <span class="border border-slate-300 px-3 py-2">Event-driven architecture</span>
        <span class="border border-slate-300 px-3 py-2">Record linkage</span>
        <span class="border border-slate-300 px-3 py-2">Query optimization</span>
        <span class="border border-slate-300 px-3 py-2">Production recovery</span>
        <span class="border border-slate-300 px-3 py-2">Observability</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="flex flex-col justify-end gap-5">
      <article class="border-t border-slate-300 pt-5">
        <p class="font-lexend text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
          Query optimization
        </p>
        <strong class="mt-2 block font-lexend text-4xl font-bold text-slate-950">
          8-22s -> sub-600ms
        </strong>
        <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
          Separated analytical reads from transactional database paths so large stock-screener results could load in under a second instead of tens of seconds.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="border-t border-slate-300 pt-5">
        <p class="font-lexend text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
          Event reliability
        </p>
        <strong class="mt-2 block font-lexend text-4xl font-bold text-slate-950">
          Idempotent job processing
        </strong>
        <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
          Made notification workers safe under retries, duplicate messages, shutdowns, and delayed processing.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="border-t border-slate-300 pt-5">
        <p class="font-lexend text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
          Multi-source entity resolution
        </p>
        <strong class="mt-2 block font-lexend text-4xl font-bold text-slate-950">
          Canonical records from messy sources
        </strong>
        <p class="mt-3 text-slate-600">
          Linked records for the same real-world entity across independent sources, then produced stable canonical records with evidence scoring, resumable runs, conflict cleanup, and traceable audit history.
        </p>
      </article>
    </aside>
